<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubizomb.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bizomb</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Fatcat </span><br>  Posts: 922<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/3/02 8:41:24 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: HASTE &gt; ALL. why do some 50+ not have any?</span><hr size=1> How does a percentage increase improve 1 thing more than another?<br>
21% increase on 44 delay is still a 21% increase.<br>
21% increase on a 22 delay is a 21% increase. <br>
<br>
The absolute number is different, but they are still both getting the same relative increase in output.<br>
<br>
The argument that haste affects weapons differently is false. <br>
It adds a percent increase to all weapons. And it adds the same percent increase to all weapons. It acts on all weapons the same way. <br>
What their virtual ratio ends up being doesn't matter. They are still FAR better than they were without haste.<br>
<br>
If I could only get haste in my chest slot and I had the choice between a shining bp and a 40% haste no stats bp I would choose the 40% haste bp. And I would be far far better off than the unhasted person wearing the shining bp.<br>
Haste is that significant. It does make that much of a difference in your performance.<br>
<br>
Biz.<br>
