<br>
I'm a Mathematician, I know these things inside and out.  Ratios are <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> vital</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
Am I saying that an &quot;uber&quot; weapon obviates the need for Haste?  Not at all.<br>
<br>
Am I saying that if you have to chose between upgrading your Haste and upgrading your weapons that you should put some thought into the choice?  Yes, most deffinitely.<br>
<br>
Let's put it this way...<br>
<br>
Assume you have a weapon with a 35/39 ratio (to avoid the whole 40+ delay damage bonus issue) and a 16% Haste belt... both sell-able for <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> approximately</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> the same price.<br>
Now, assume that you have barely enough cash so that if you sold either your Weapon or your Belt, you could buy <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> either</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> a 32/35 weapon <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> or</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> a 22% Haste belt.<br>
<br>
Which do you buy?<br>
<br>
According to my calculations, you're better off buying the 32/35 weapon.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> How does a percentage increase improve 1 thing more than another?<br>
21% increase on 44 delay is still a 21% increase.<br>
21% increase on a 22 delay is a 21% increase. <br>
<br>
The absolute number is different, but they are still both getting the same relative increase in output.<br>
<br>
The argument that haste affects weapons differently is false. <br>
It adds a percent increase to all weapons. And it adds the same percent increase to all weapons. It acts on all weapons the same way. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
This is patently incorrect.  It has been proven that Haste does not <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> increase</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> a weapon's speed... it <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> reduces</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> a weapon's delay.<br>
<br>
Therefore Haste is much more efficient on an 60/60 weapon (extreme, none-existant example) than it is on a 20/20 weapon. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubizomb.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bizomb</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Fatcat </span><br>  Posts: 929<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/3/02 12:57:37 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: HASTE &gt; ALL. why do some 50+ not have any?</span><hr size=1> Certainly upgrading your weapons and haste is a choice you have to make. <br>
Obviously you can work out which will get you the most bang for your buck a big weapon increase or a big haste increase. Once you've got the big weapon tho are you saying you shouldn't bother trying to get that 22% haste increase too?<br>
